&gt; How about using AOP bytecode weaving for replacing the calls to
&gt; System.exit() with your fake implementation?
&gt;
&gt; Perhaps something like this:
&gt;
&gt; public aspect SystemExitTestingAspect {
&gt;
&gt;   pointcut systemExit(int reason) :
&gt;     call(java.lang.System.exit(int)) && args(reason);
&gt;
&gt;   void around(int reason) : systemExit(reason) {
&gt;     fake.java.lang.System.exit(reason);
&gt;   }
&gt; }
&gt;
&gt; Sounds like a very neat solution, however I am not sure how you would do
this with the JDK classes.
